The numbers on the spiral are placed on the integer lattice with  

\[
1\;(0,0),\;2\;(1,0),\;3\;(1,1),\;4\;(0,1),\;5\,(-1,1),\;6\,(-1,0),\;7\,(-1,-1),\;8\,(0,-1),\;9\,(1,-1),\dots
\]

For a point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
k=\max\{|x|,|y|\}
\]

be the “layer’’ of the spiral.  
The greatest number in layer \(k\) is  

\[
M_k=(2k+1)^2 \qquad\text{and}\qquad N_{k,0}=M_{k-1}+1=(2k-1)^2+1 .
\]

Going round the layer we have  

* **right side** \((k,\,y),\;y=-(k-1)\ldots k\):
\[
n = (2k-1)^2 + y + k .
\]

* **bottom side** \((x,\,-k),\;x=-k+1\ldots k\):
\[
n = (2k-1)^2 +7k + x .
\]

(Other sides are not needed here.)

---

### Coordinates of the eight neighbours of \(2026\)

First locate 2026.  
It lies at \((23,-22)\) (first cell of layer \(k=23\)):
\[
(2\cdot23-1)^2+(-22)+23 = 2025-22+23 = 2026 .
\]

The eight surrounding lattice points are  

\[
\begin{array}{ccl}
(22,-23) & &\text{(bottom side, }k=23)\\
(23,-23) & &\text{corner }(k,-k)\\
(24,-23) & &\text{right side of layer }24\\[2mm]
(22,-22) & &\text{corner }(k,-k)\text{ of layer }22\\
(24,-22) & &\text{right side of layer }24\\[2mm]
(22,-21) & &\text{right side of layer }22\\
(23,-21) & &\text{right side of layer }23\\
(24,-21) & &\text{right side of layer }24
\end{array}
\]

Now evaluate each using the formulas.

| \((x,y)\) | layer \(k\) | number \(n\) |
|-----------|-----------|--------------|
| (22,-23) | 23 | \( (2\!\cdot\!23-1)^2 + 7\!\cdot\!23 +22 = 2025+161+22 = 2208\) |
| (23,-23) | 23 | \(M_{23}= (2\!\cdot\!23+1)^2 = 47^{2}=2209\) |
| (24,-23) | 24 | \( (2\!\cdot\!24-1)^2 + (-23)+24 = 2209-23+24 = 2210\) |
| (22,-22) | 22 | \(M_{22}= (2\!\cdot\!22+1)^2 =45^{2}=2025\) |
| (24,-22) | 24 | \( (2\!\cdot\!24-1)^2 + (-22)+24 = 2211\) |
| (22,-21) | 22 | \( (2\!\cdot\!22-1)^2 + (-21)+22 = 1849-21+22 = 1850\) |
| (23,-21) | 23 | \(2025+(-21)+23 = 2027\) |
| (24,-21) | 24 | \(2209-21+24 = 2212\) |

Adding them:

\[
\begin{aligned}
&2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212 \\[2mm]
&= 16\,952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16\,952}
\]
